	 Muzaffarnagar (PTI): A Muzaffarnagar court has sentenced a man to life imprisonment for burning his son alive. Nine family members deposed in the court, official sources said. Jamil Ahmed, 55, set Rashid, 19, on fire while he was sleeping allegedly because his son had been opposed to the sale of their house.                  
	 Coimbatore (PTI): Manonmanian Sundaranar University in Tamil Nadu is introducing a postgraduate course in nano-biotechnology, a combination of biotechnology and nanotechnology, claimed to be a first in the country, from this year. The course is research-based that will cater to industry needs.                  
	 New Delhi: The Prime Minister has approved G.K. Pillai as the next Union home secretary after Madhukar Gupta retires at the end of the month. Pillai takes over as officer on special duty in the home ministry from June 11 before taking over as home secretary. Rahul Khullar will take over as commerce secretary from Pillai.                   
	 Aligarh (PTI): A.R. Rahman will be awarded an honorary DLit degree by Aligarh Muslim University at its annual convocation on June 7. Bengal Governor Gopalkrishna Gandhi will be the chief guest at the convocation.                                                                                                                           
